            Who we are
            We are a registered non-profit organization and a local chapter of R-Ladies Global. Our aim is to promote gender diversity in the R community, both in Australia and worldwide. We are proudly a community of over 2000 members!
            R-Ladies Melbourne Inc welcomes members of all R proficiency levels, whether you‚Äôre a new or aspiring R user, or an experienced R programmer interested in mentoring, networking & expert upskilling. Our community is designed to develop our members‚Äô R skills & knowledge through social, collaborative learning & sharing.
            Meet our 2021-2022 commitee here.
            
            
            What we do
            We host regular meet-ups, usually once or twice a month. We cover a range of topics from intro to advanced - for more information, visit our events page. You can also find slides and materials from our past events at our Github page and view most of our event recordings on our Youtube channel.
            
            
            Join our community
            Follow us and join our vibrant online community on Twitter @RLadiesMelb to stay up-to-date with our events and activities. We are always on the look out for speakers so do get in touch if you are interested!
            
            
            Our sponsors
            IMAGE WITH LOGOS
            And special thanks to Roberto Bonelli for creating our gorgeous logo.
